Cell[TextData[{
 "Figure 9.  Forward-model solves to reach a target accuracy on the predicted \
concentration. Because MC needs ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"O", "(", 
    SuperscriptBox["tol", 
     RowBox[{"-", "2"}]], ")"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"f005a074-6b5b-42d4-ad95-7be7047ed0a9"],
 " and QMC ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"O", "(", 
    SuperscriptBox["tol", 
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], ")"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"b637158f-271c-4cf1-9e13-fe9c291b8459"],
 ", the gap widens with the accuracy demanded: ~2\[Times] at 1%, ~4\[Times] \
at 0.5%, ~18\[Times] at 0.1%."
}], "Text",
 CellMargins->{{45, 40}, {2, 14}},
 FontSize->11.5,
 FontSlant->Italic,
 FontColor->GrayLevel[
  0.4],ExpressionUUID->"5be7b1d6-377d-4806-9935-e6d194ba12f8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "That is the value proposition in one figure. QMC changes neither the model \
nor the estimand \[LongDash] only ",
 StyleBox["which points you evaluate at",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " \[LongDash] and that single swap buys back most of an order of magnitude \
in expensive model runs."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"514548f4-8a7b-438d-81f1-2d9f289ae563"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["11.  The cover animation", "Section",
 FontColor->RGBColor[
  0.153, 0.51, 0.64],ExpressionUUID->"9c9f6882-bbbe-4635-a4c1-b80ab316528d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For completeness, here is the code behind the animation at the top \
\[LongDash] the same Monte-Carlo and Sobol\[CloseCurlyQuote] point sets \
accumulating, with the running integration error traced beneath. It is the \
whole post compressed into ",
 StyleBox["1/N",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " versus ",
 StyleBox["1/\[Sqrt]N",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0df3151b-9fb5-4ab8-94f6-41ef087fb07d"],

Cell["\<\
frameNs = Round[2^Range[3, 12]];
fInt[pt_] := Exp[Total[pt]];   exact = (E - 1.)^2;
mcAll  = BlockRandom[SeedRandom[7]; RandomReal[1, {4096, 2}]];
sobAll = LDPoints[\"Sobol\", 4096, 2];
runErr[pts_] := Abs[Mean[fInt /@ pts] - exact];
(* each frame: MC cloud | Sobol cloud, with the error-vs-N race below *)
frames = Table[ Rasterize @ Column[{
     Row[{ListPlot[mcAll[[1 ;; n]]], ListPlot[sobAll[[1 ;; n]]]}],
     ListLogLogPlot[{ {#, runErr[mcAll[[1 ;; #]]]} & /@ Select[frameNs, # <= \
n &],
                      {#, runErr[sobAll[[1 ;; #]]]} & /@ Select[frameNs, # <= \
n &] },
        Joined -> True] }], {n, frameNs}];
Export[\"hero.gif\", AnimatedImage[frames, FrameRate -> 1.4]]\
\>", "Program",
 ShowStringCharacters->False,
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.96, 0.97, 0.98],ExpressionUUID->"d520ecf4-ba12-4022-abf5-c9275632ecd3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["12.  Conclusions", "Section",
 FontColor->RGBColor[
  0.153, 0.51, 0.64],ExpressionUUID->"b04b588a-fe59-4230-98f7-839306b26cac"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "On the posterior of a real six-parameter pharmacokinetic fit, deterministic \
low-discrepancy sampling beats plain Monte Carlo by close to a full power of ",
 StyleBox["N",
  FontFamily->"Times",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " \[LongDash] measured slopes near ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"-", "0.95"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "113e37ff-291e-4387-b6b1-6e7736c0ee60"],
 " against ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"-", "0.5"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "60684785-2011-4c5b-91b6-ab0a3d8f1cb0"],
 ", and a 2\[Times]\[Dash]18\[Times] saving in model evaluations (up to an \
order of magnitude at the tightest tolerances). Against classical least \
squares, the Bayesian treatment adds honest, regularized uncertainty where an \
unidentifiable model would otherwise report nonsense error bars \[LongDash] \
and QMC is what makes computing that uncertainty cheap."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"62e84f5d-4340-4423-b958-0a4908da95da"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["When QMC helps, and when it does not.",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " It helps when the dimension is low-to-moderate or the effective dimension \
is small, the integrand is smooth, and evaluations are the bottleneck. It \
does not help for rough or discontinuous integrands, very high dimension, or \
heavy-tailed importance weights \[LongDash] which is why we integrate against \
a smooth Gaussianized posterior rather than a spiky ratio."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dad9d23c-b535-4863-970e-fce4e4bd65ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["The portable recipe.",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " (1) reparameterize to an unconstrained space and build a Gaussian \
approximation of the posterior; (2) map the unit cube through it with the \
inverse-CDF transform; (3) swap your pseudo-random draws for a randomized \
Sobol\[CloseCurlyQuote] or Halton set; (4) average over a few randomizations \
for an error bar. Two lines of change, most of an order of magnitude back."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"07e448ea-a43c-44b6-8661-01a8b39770e9"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["13.  References & reproducibility", "Section",
 FontColor->RGBColor[
  0.153, 0.51, 0.64],ExpressionUUID->"8069c131-e3ad-438a-86b3-b94d6ccc638d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Halton, J. H.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (1960). ",
 StyleBox["Numerische Mathematik",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " 2, 84\[Dash]90.  \[Bullet]  ",
