  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (2008). ",
 StyleBox["SIAM J. Sci. Comput.",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " 30, 2635\[Dash]2654 (the direction numbers used here)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9b7a555c-299c-4f27-b49e-c171c7bba051"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Niederreiter, H.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (1992). ",
 StyleBox["Random Number Generation and Quasi-Monte Carlo Methods",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ", SIAM.  \[Bullet]  ",
 StyleBox["Caflisch, R. E.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (1998). ",
 StyleBox["Acta Numerica",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " 7, 1\[Dash]49 (effective dimension).  \[Bullet]  ",
 StyleBox["Owen, A. B.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (1998). ",
 StyleBox["J. Complexity",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " 14, 466\[Dash]489 (randomized QMC).  \[Bullet]  ",
 StyleBox["Gerber, M., & Chopin, N.",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (2015). ",
 StyleBox["JRSS B",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " 77, 509\[Dash]579 (QMC in Bayesian computation)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8b3cb4fc-472c-4b44-8f1e-477f349ba693"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Boeckmann, Sheiner & Beal",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (1994). ",
 StyleBox["NONMEM Users Guide",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " (the Theophylline data).  \[Bullet]  ",
 StyleBox["Gabrielsson & Weiner",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (2016). ",
 StyleBox["Pharmacokinetic and Pharmacodynamic Data Analysis",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " (the two-compartment model)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e10f4c38-24a9-4153-a013-e46235137630"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "All code is pure Wolfram Language at ",
 StyleBox["github.com/mthiel74/QuasiMonteCarloBayesianEstimation",
  FontWeight->"SemiBold"],
 " (",
 StyleBox["https://github.com/mthiel74/QuasiMonteCarloBayesianEstimation",
  FontFamily->"Source Code Pro",
  FontSize->10],
 ")",
 ". The companion package ",
 StyleBox["qmc_bayes_helpers.wl",
  FontFamily->"Source Code Pro",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0.153, 0.51, 0.64]],
 " is the single source of truth; the figure scripts and this notebook both \
load it. To rebuild:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"893bd317-b78a-41f2-9fae-8368f74c18e6"],

Cell["\<\
wolframscript -file wolfram/fetch_theoph.wls   # real data -> data/
wolframscript -file wolfram/run_all.wls        # all figures -> docs/images/
wolframscript -file community/build_notebook.wls\
\>", "Program",
